<DOCNO> AP881223-0007 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
sketches of four key figures in the new israeli 
cabinet 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
prime minister yitzhak shamir leader of the rightwing likud 
bloc retains his post in the new government a former underground 
fighter and mossad secret agent shamir has been characterized as a 
politician with the tenacity of a bulldog 
he has rejected any negotiations with the palestine liberation 
oganization and is opposed to calls for an international peace 
conference on the middle east but he has pledged to introduce new 
peace proposals after his new government is in place 
shamir 73 was born in poland and emigrated to what was then 
palestine in 1938 a decade before the founding of israel he has a 
law degree and did not enter politics until 1956 he served as prime 
minister in 198384 and again starting oct 14 1986 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
shimon peres moves to the finance ministry from the foreign 
ministry the son of a polish timber merchant he arrived in 
palestine in 1934 and as a teenager delivered messages on his 
motorcycle for israels founding father david bengurion 
peres 65 has written at least four books and has said that in 
his youth he wanted to be a poet he is seen as an intellectual but 
many israelis also view him as arrogant and distant 
peres oncedominant labor party has won national elections only 
once in the past 11 years and the 1983 victory was not by a 
sufficient margin to allow labor to rule without likud peres favors 
an international peace conference and has promoted the idea of a 
dialogue with palestinians in confederation with jordan 
as finance minister peres will have to confront growing budget 
deficits and major financial problems in israels industries 
including companies owned by the laborallied histadrut union 
federation 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
yitzhak rabin remains defense minister a post he held when the 
israeli cabinet voted to withdraw its invading force from lebanon 
after a threeyear occupation a native of jerusalem he was 
ambassador to the united states from 196873 
his term as prime minister was cut short in 1977 when he was 
forced to resign in a scandal over his wifes illegal overseas bank 
accounts he and peres have had a long rivalry for leadership of the 
labor party 
rabin 66 fought in world war ii taking part in allied 
operations in syria and fighting behind enemy lines he was army 
chief of staff during the 1967 sixday war in which israel took 
control of the west bank gaza strip and golan heights from 
neighboring arab countries 
he has ordered a firm response to the yearold palestinian 
uprising in the occupied territories 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
moshe arens replaces peres as foreign minister a native of 
lithuania he immigrated with his family to the united states at the 
age of 14 and studied aeronautical engineering at the california 
institute of technology and the massachusetts institute of 
technology 
he moved to israel in 1950 and is said to be proudest of the 
planes and missiles he designed here both for the israeli military 
and for export 
colleagues describe arens as cool and thoughtful he was 
ambassador to the united states in 198283 and he is likely to be 
heavily engaged in dialogue with washington following the us 
decision to open talks with the plo which israel considers a 
terrorist organization 
arens 62 is an extreme conservative and reportedly turned down 
the job of defense minister in 1980 because he opposed the 
justconcluded israelegypt peace treaty 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP881223-0008 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the decision by pan american world airways and 
the us government not to alert the public to a fairly specific 
bomb threat received long before pan am flight 103 crashed in 
scotland could raise liability problems for the airline but probably 
not for the government attorneys say 
i dont know of any legal requirement that the us go public 
on a thing like that other than notifying the airline involved and 
possibly the embassies said lee kreindler a new york lawyer who 
specializes in aviation accident cases 
its a difficult area but if the government notifies the 
airline in question i think the government position is justified 
kreindler said thursday 
kreindler said there are some policy reasons from the 
governments standpoint for not notifying the traveling public 
one of the purposes of the federal aviation act is to enhance 
aviation and an announcement of a specific threat which might not be 
bona fide could conceivably result in travelers not flying 
flight 103 originating in frankfurt west germany with a change 
of planes at londons heathrow airport crashed in scotland on 
wednesday killing all 258 people aboard and more than 20 on the 
ground it was bound for new york 
phyllis oakley a state department spokeswoman said that an 
unidentified individual telephoned the us embassy in helsinki on 
dec 5 and said there would be a bombing attempt within two weeks 
against a pan am aircraft flying from frankfurt to the united states 
the conduit would be an unwitting passenger who would take 
the device from helsinki to frankfurt and then board a usbound 
flight she said 
it has not been established however that the telephoned tip was 
related to the pan am crash 
mrs oakley said dozens of threats are received each day and all 
are taken seriously l paul bremer who heads the state 
departments counterterrorism office said there have been 87 calls 
similar to the helsinki call over the past three months 
but the dec 5 call apparently from a tipster appeared to be 
taken more seriously than most others many us embassies were 
apprised of the threat including the american mission in moscow 
where a notice of the threat was posted on a bulletin board 
no word went out to the general public 
the prior notification is going to raise an interesting 
question in connection with the other passengers who were not 
members of the state department staff whether they should have 
received similar notice from pan am said george n tompkins jr 
a lawyer specializing in defending airlines in accident cases 
bremer said in an interview thursday night that not enough is 
known to conclude that sabotage caused the jumbo jet to crash 
we dont know if this is a terrorist attack he said 
asked what an airlines obligation is once it has been notified 
of a specific threat kreindler said its a tough situation 
they dont have to stop operating or stop flying but certainly they 
have a duty to meticulously inspect 
kreindler said that in some other instances of terrorism 
involving air travel evidencegathering in lawsuits has focused on 
airline security precautions 
officials said pan am stepped up security at key airports in the 
wake of the threat 
anyone filing lawsuits seeking settlements in excess of a 75000 
limit in international airlines cases would have to show willful 
misconduct on the part of the airline in order to be successful 
tompkins said willful misconduct is extremely difficult to prove 
carrying with it a heavier burden of proof than gross negligence 
willful misconduct is a wrongful act done intentionally or an 
improper act done wantonly with knowledge of the probable 
consequences 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP881223-0009 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the damage to national security caused by a 
soldier accused of spying for the warsaw pact might not be as severe 
as originally feared pentagon officials say 
the officials who insisted on anonymity said thursday that 
continuing interrogation of warrant officer james william hall iii 
suggests he might have been selective in the documents he passed 
when all is said and done it doesnt look too bad said one 
official 
its not great but its not a crisis either said another 
the counterintelligence people are wringing him out now 
said one source hes still cooperating singing 
hall 30 of new york city was arrested wednesday at his home 
near fort stewart ga by army intelligence agents after a 
successful armyfbi sting operation 
lt col john chapla an army spokesman said hall was moved 
thursday from fort stewart to a prison cell at fort meade md 
outside washington dc 
according to affidavits filed in federal court in savannah ga 
where fort stewart is located hall bragged to an unidentified fbi 
agent that he had been passing highly sensitive signal 
intelligence documents to both the soviets and the east german 
intelligence services since late 1982 
hall boasted of the important signal intelligence information 
he had passed and admitted his motivation to be greed the 
document said it did not give details on the information 
hall allegedly passed the information through a turkishborn 
naturalized citizen named huseyin yildirim yildirim also was 
arrested wednesday at his home in belleair beach fla near st 
petersburg 
he had been scheduled to appear at a bond hearing thursday but 
the proceeding was postponed until tuesday because yildirims 
attorney had a scheduling conflict 
chapla said hall was moved to facilitate security noting the 
base at fort meade has secure facilities that can be used for 
courtsmartial that involve the presentation of classified material 
as evidence 
fort meade also is the site of the national security agency the 
supersecret spy agency that conducts electronic surveillance around 
the world hall worked in the field of electronic surveillance for 
the army and indirectly the nsa 
the spokesman declined to say whether nsa specialists were 
sitting in on the interrogation of hall 
chapla said hall not been formally charged with any crimes as of 
thursday evening but was being detained under the uniform code of 
military justice for suspicion of espionage he can be held for up 
to three days on that basis chapla said 
according to army records hall held a top secret security 
clearance and spent most of his 12 years in the service at posts in 
west germany where the army maintains electronic listening posts 
and intelligence units that would play critical roles in time of war 
during his service career hall rose in rank to a point where he 
could have provided a detailed and damaging look at our techniques 
and capabilities when it comes to intercepting radio and voice 
traffic and breaking codes explained one official 
but weve got to find out how far he went he could have kept 
his handlers happy with less sensitive stuff too 
added an army source he was a worker bee he had familiarity 
with the techniques and technology of the business of signals 
intelligence its logical to say he could have really hurt us 
chapla said hall had been flown on an army airplane from fort 
stewart to fort meade on thursday afternoon and that in the process 
legal jurisdiction over the warrant officer was shifted to the 
commander of the military district of washington 
that commander is maj gen donald c hilbert should 
investigators recommend a grand jurytype proceeding and court 
martial it will be up to hilbert to decide how to proceed chapla 
