fairness opinions often get higher fees if the deal goes 
through the opinions offer conclusions on the fairness of a buyout 
offer 
asked by rep mike synar dokla whether fairness opinions were 
independent ruder said all in all i am quite suspicious in a 
significant number of cases that the fairness opinion is prepared 
by somebody with an incentive to go along with management 
personally i think that needs to be addressed 
ruder said he was giving the house energy and commerce 
telecommunications and finance subcommittee his personal opinion 
not that of the sec which is currently reviewing all aspects of 
leveraged buyouts 
leveraged buyouts occur when investors borrow heavily to buy out 
a company and then pay off the debt with that companys cash flow or 
by the sale of its assets 
ruder said the commission wants to determine whether it should 
issue new rules to protect investors and predicted the review would 
continue at least through february 
fairness opinions are primary factors in the transactions ruder 
said because shareholders accord a great degree of weight to the 
fact that a favorable opinion has been issued 
the opinions usually attest that the price offered for shares of 
a company is a fair one 
the hired financial adviser must rely almost exclusively on the 
limited information that management supplies about the company 
