<TEXT>
reflecting the climate of detente between 
the united states and the soviet union the united nations 43rd 
general assembly concluded its most harmonious session 
the buoyant sometimes tumultuous session that ended thursday was 
highlighted by president reagans farewell mikhail s gorbachevs 
showstopping debut and the assemblys decision for the first time 
to leave new york and travel to geneva to hear yasser arafat 
the 12week session adopted most resolutions by consensus 
including for the first time the afghanistan resolution 
recognizing the soviet troop withdrawal 
it adopted the un budget without a divisive note wednesday 
the first time the financial plan was adopted without a vote since 
the world body was founded 42 years ago 
the 199091 budget of 176 billion was about 22 million less 
than the last its adoption by consensus and the lower expenditure 
were viewed as a us victory 
dante caputo the general assembly president and argentinas 
foreign minister told the closing session the assembly had 
benefited from the new international climate of detente and 
cooperation between the united states and the soviet union and had 
contributed to it 
caputo said the consensus within the 159member assembly was 
unprecedented in the history of the organization 
the world body even charmed its most strident critic the united 
states which committed itself during the session to repay nearly 
500 million owed to the un budget and peacekeeping forces the 
money had been withheld for years for ideological budgetary and 
other reasons 
relations strained during most of the eightyear reagan 
administration eased considerably and when reagan delivered his 
final speech in september he praised the world body for its 
peacekeeping and peacemaking in afghanistan iran and iraq and 
elsewhere 
