<TEXT>
plo chairman yasser arafat today blamed terrorists 
for the crash of the pan am jetliner in scotland condemning it as 
an inhuman criminal action that undermines the peace process in 
the middle east 
at a news conference at the end of his oneday visit to rome 
arafat made his first public comment on the crash of the boeing 747 
in lockerbie scotland that killed all 258 people aboard and at 
least 22 on the ground 
this is an inhuman criminal action which we condemn arafat 
said it is against our peace mission it is not against a state 
it is directed against humanity as a whole it is another proof that 
we should all fight against this type of terrorist act 
we join other nations in an effort to stop this terrorism and 
criminal acts he added 
the united states last week reversed a 13year policy and opened 
a substantive dialogue with the plo after arafat renounced 
terrorism and accepted israels right to exist us officials have 
said the talks will be scuttled if there is proof of plo involvement 
in terrorism 
arafat said he was very sad because the pan am crash claimed 
the life of one of my friends referring to bernt carlsson the 
un official involved in negotiations for independence of namibia 
i send my heartfelt condolences to all the victims of this 
crime 
investigators in britain are trying to determine if the pan am 
plane was destroyed by a bomb foreign minister moshe arens of 
israel on friday linked the crash to palestinian factions 
i am really astonished that rumors were directed against the 
palestinians only arafat said 
asked whether he could control terrorist abu nidal and other 
radical palestinian factions he said these groups are not 
palestinian groups they follow the intelligence of several arab and 
other states 
arafat said he could only account for groups and individuals 
under the plo flag he claimed the israeli secret service mossad 
was trying to undermine the usplo dialogue 
according to my information the mossad has already received 
their orders from the israeli government to sabotage the peace 
process he said he did not elaborate 
it is very important for everyone to know we are pushing to 
achieve peace not only the palestinian leadership but our masses 
arafat said we are against all forms of terrorism 
he said mossad and other groups posed a greater threat all of 
us have to coordinate efforts to face all forms of terrorism he 
said 
