an air india jumbo jet bound for new york with 250 
people aboard returned to london today after a bomb threat 
also today a terminal at heathrow airport was evacuated after 
officials spotted a suspicious suitcase and a british airways 
tristar flew to heathrow after a bomb threat forced it to make an 
unscheduled stop in rome on thursday 
all three incidents followed wednesdays explosion of a new 
yorkbound pan am boeing 747 over the scottish village of lockerbie 
all 258 people aboard were killed along with at least 22 people on 
the ground 
after air india flight 109 a boeing 747 had taken off for new 
york at 259 pm air india in new york received a bomb threat from 
an anonymous caller said an airline spokesman who demanded 
anonymity 
the bomb threat as a matter of routine was passed to the 
captain of flight 109 who decided to return to heathrow the 
spokesman said 
the 747 landed at 421 pm and taxied to an isolated area 
southwest of the terminals where emergency services were standing 
by the british airports authority said 
passengers left the plane normally and were taken by bus to 
terminal three where they were being kept in two rooms the airline 
spokesman said the plane would be thoroughly searched 
earlier today an unattended suitcase prompted officials to 
evacuate hundreds of christmas travelers from terminal three but a 
bomb squad found the bag contained just clothing airport officials 
said 
the british airports authority said the suitcase was found about 
noon today next to an air canada checkin desk just one aisle away 
from the pan am checkin counter 
police said they were told that a man walked into the terminal 
left the suitcase and drove off again 
