commandos with explosive charges 
attacked the defense ministry and military headquarters in the 
capital today military sources said no casualties were immediately 
reported 
it was the first time the installation which houses the defense 
ministry and the joint chiefs of staff was attacked during 
salvadors nineyear guerrilla war 
the sources who spoke on condition of anonymity gave no other 
details 
radio reports indicated that two car bombs detonated near the 
walled compound in the southwest part of the city but the reports 
could not be immediately confirmed 
no one claimed responsibility but the attackers were presumed to 
