richard b setlow of upton ny will receive the energy 
departments enrico fermi award for 1988 the department announced 
friday 
the award a gold medal and 100000 for each is given for 
exceptional and altogether outstanding achievement in the 
development use or control of atomic energy 
weisskopf 80 is a professor at massachusetts institute of 
technology his citation said he was being honored for many unique 
contributions to particle and nuclear physics and to physics in 
general as a researcher educator and statesman of science 
setlow 67 is a biophysicist on the staff of the brookhaven 
national laboratory he was honored for pioneering and 
farreaching contributions to the fields of radiation biophysics and 
molecular biology beginning with the discovery and 
conceptualization of the processes of dna repair that have had an 
impact on research in genetics recombination mutation and 
carcinogenesis 
the award is named for the late enrico fermi who fled fascist 
italy for the united states before world war ii and who achieved the 
first selfsustaining nuclear chain reaction in 1942 during the 
manhattan project which developed the atomic bomb 
