the cockpit recording of pan am flight 
103s final minutes ended with a brief mysterious faint noise 
and gave no sign that the pilots knew their boeing 747 was doomed 
investigators said friday 
conversations captured by the black box that records all 
cockpit activity was normal up to the faint noise at the end which 
needs a bit more analysis said paul mckie a department of 
transport spokesman 
mick charles of the departments air accident investigation 
branch who is heading a team of 40 us and british investigators 
at the crash site said we have no evidence whatsoever yet of 
sabotage 
the plane flying from london to new york broke up at 31000 
feet wednesday night killing all 258 people aboard and bombarding 
the scottish countryside with flaming wreckage over a 10mile radius 
flowers arrived at the scene friday a passenger who had left the 
