disclosure of the faa bulletin in early december the 23rd such 
alert this year has prompted questions over whether such notices 
should be shared with the public 
president reagan said earlier friday that a public warning based 
on an anonymous telephone call as was the case with the alert 
involving pan am would have been an overreaction it would 
literally have closed down air traffic in the world reagan said 
