<TEXT>
after settling the nations biggest securities 
fraud case drexel burnham lambert inc now faces the crucial task 
of retaining its clients who include many wellknown takeover 
strategists 
the beleaguered wall street firm received some staunch support 
from a number of corporate clients thursday one day after it 
agreeing to plead guilty to six fraud charges and pay the government 
a record 650 million penalty 
but some clients said privately they still needed to review 
whether the pleabargaining arrangement would change their close 
business relationship with drexel 
i dont think anything at this point is that clear said a 
spokesman for one client which did not want to be identified 
