what could have been a lengthy costly trial that threatened to 
slowly destroy the firm the government had spent two years 
investigating drexels relationship with ivan f boesky the former 
stock speculator was accused of insider trading 
although the 650 million settlement is the largest ever in a 
securities fraud case drexel said it may have cost more in lost 
business and legal fees had it continued to fight the federal 
charges frederick h joseph drexel chief executive officer said 
the company already has lost about 15 billion in business and paid 
out 175 million in legal expenses 
the settlement though does not protect michael milken drexels 
highyield junk bond whiz and another key target of the criminal 
probe milken repeatedly has asserted his innocence 
drexel now faces the formidable task of retaining its key 
clientele even without milken if it hopes to remain one of the 
most powerful and profitable investment banks on wall street 
milken has generated billions of dollars in revenue for drexel 
through junk bond underwriting much of which has been used to 
finance some of the biggest corporate takeovers of the decade 
