memory chips hitachi officials said 
the agreement announced thursday calls for jointly developing 
16megabit drams or dynamic random access memory chips by 
exchanging technology 
a 16megabit dram can hold 16 million bits of information 
equivalent to about 64 pages of an englishlanguage newspaper and 
16 times the size of the 1megabit drams commonly used in todays 
highperformance computers 
each company will have access to the others dram technology 
as it relates to 16megabit development hitachi said in a 
statement 
we are very happy to enter into this relationship with 
hitachi william p weber texas instruments executive vice 
president said in a statement both of our companies bring unique 
technological skills in drams 
he said the agreement which only covers technology related to 
16megabit chips will be expanded to cover other future generation 
technology the threeyear agreement is extendable a hitachi 
official said 
