<TEXT>
lockheed corp said today it had 
buttressed its takeover defenses following the disclosure that 
dallas investor harold c simmons intended to boost his holdings in 
the aerospace firm 
lockheed spokesman bob slayman refused to say if the changes in a 
2yearold poison pill shareholder rights plan were a direct 
response to simmons move nor would he reveal if lockheed builder 
of the stealth fighter and other military hardware had discussed 
the investment with simmons 
simmons did not immediately respond to a telephone request for 
comment 
according to lockheed simmons valhi inc filed notice under the 
hartscottrodino act that he intended to boost his lockheed stake 
beyond 15 million the trigger point for the acts disclosure 
provisions 
as of the dec 7 filing valhi said it owned 375000 of 
lockheeds 595 million outstanding shares or 063 percent 
a lockheed board vote to tighten the firms takeover defenses was 
taken thursday two weeks after the filing slayman said 
the amendment is intended to heighten the protection afforded 
shareholders against abusive takeover tactics the company said in 
a news release 
the revised plan allows present shareholders to buy newly issued 
stock at a discount if an outsider buys 20 percent or more of the 
common stock those rights can be canceled if the independent 
directors determine the takeover bid is in the best interest of 
shareholders or if the company cancels the rights within 10 days of 
the time outside holdings reach 20 percent 
such poison pill plans are intended to dilute the holdings of a 
potential buyer making a takeover prohibitively expensive 
lockheed with headquarters in this los angeles suburb has 
88000 employees in california georgia new jersey texas and new 
hampshire the nations fourthlargest defense contractor lockheed 
had sales of 113 billion in 1987 
in the first three quarters of this year it reported a net 
profit of 520 million on sales of 76 billion with the profit 
figure boosted significantly by sale of a subsidiary 
besides the f117a stealth fighter its proojects include the 
trident ii nuclear missile the c5b transport plane and work on 
military communications satellites and the strategic defense 
initiative or star wars the company also is a subcontractor for 
design work on nasas space station project 
